<font color="#FF0000">THE MISSING-THE ABANDONED</font><br>
<tt>Sun Mar 16 22:15:05 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
One of the most sobering discoveries I had to accept as a Nam vet was that some American somewhere made a decision about writing off American fighting men-deciding to leave those men to the mercy of an enemy of little mercy.  Even now it is difficult to conceive of any scenario that could justify such a decision.  Only as I was able to admit and see my own personal depravity was I able to finally see that yes, this national sin was indeed possible.  I feel that this open forum is a necessary thing.  We have to discuss this and decide how to heal ourselves of this horror.  We must somehow suffer this fatal wound and see if our survival is possible.  We may find that after-all we really didn't make it home from Nam. 
